**Affected versions**
* 65.0b4, 86.0a1 (2020-12-20), 84.0.1, 78.6esr;

**Affected platforms**
* macOS 10.15, Windows 10, Ubuntu 16;

**Steps to reproduce**
1. Launch Firefox, access about:preferences#privacy
2. Scroll down to the Permissions section;
3. Click on the Settings button for [Location, Camera, Microphone, Notifications, Autoplay **or** Virtual Reality];
4. On the block new requests row (one with the checkbox), hover the mouse cursor away from text (to the right);
5. Keep clicking while moving the mouse to the right;

**Expected result**
* checkbox should be toggled only while mouse is over text and checkbox;

**Actual result**
* checkbox toggle is registered over the whole inner row;

**Regression range**
* on initial implementation this option was not added, later on around 2018-01-09 / 2018-01-16 saw that only the checkbox was clickable; 
* result is only for when the text was made clickable:
* First bad: [2018-01-10](https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/pushloghtml?fromchange=e4de69553e3faf8136eb9bb7f2f741e1b7e6f866&tochange=4db166f0442dddc5b9011c722d7499501fedf283)
* Last good: [2018-01-09](https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/pushloghtml?fromchange=e4de69553e3faf8136eb9bb7f2f741e1b7e6f866&tochange=b2cb61e83ac50115a28f04aaa8a32d4db90aad23);
* Pushlog: [URL](https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/pushloghtml?fromchange=e4de69553e3faf8136eb9bb7f2f741e1b7e6f866&tochange=4db166f0442dddc5b9011c722d7499501fedf283) ;

**Additional notes**
* attached recording to best illustrate the issue;
* S4 as suggested severity since the impact is insignificant.

